      "abstract": "Abstract:The history of the reception of Foucault in China (1989-2019) is part of the process of China's reconstructing of its academic tradition after the reform and opening-up, when the control of Marxist ideology was loosened and when Western modern thought flowed into the Chinese academic community in large quantities. The Foucauldian reception can be best understood not so much in relation to previous domestic Marxist or conservative discourses, but in its competition with the thought of other Western thinkers who were introduced around the same time, such as Marin Heidegger, Max Weber, and Leo Strauss. This article studies on the one hand the broad influence of Heidegger in Philosophy, Weber in social theory and Strauss in political philosophy since the 1980s, and on the other hand how Foucault's reception has to be situated and viewed in relation to the reception of these other thinkers, negotiating its position and image in a competition that involves not only several disciplines of social sciences but also changing political positions such as the New Left, liberalism and culture conservatism in the history of China in the past forty years.",
